According to Edgar H. Schein, corporate culture can be divided into three different levels:
Level 1 - Visible Artifacts: Easy external observation factors such as appearance, symbols, symbols, languages, products, tangible culture such as architecture, design, fashion and manifestationsdifferent people can see and experience.
Level 2 - Esposeded Values: values, thinking, principles that organize publicity and share.These are the factors behind the acts and decisions of the organization and express the thinking, knowledge and views of people in the organization.
Level 3 - Basic Assumptions: These are beliefs, assumptions on how the world works, the way the organization should operate and interact.This is often not aware of the people in the organization that often exists in the unconscious form.
These levels interact with each other to create organizational culture and affect the organization of activities and interactions in the environment.

In the 4.0 era, the application of technology and digital into the health sector brings tremendous value.These solutions help people soon explore the parts of the body, in addition they also help doctors support early detection of abnormal signs that cannot be seen with the naked eye.One of the most commonly used techniques is X-ray.
 Starting in 1895, when Wilhelm R√∂ntgen accidentally discovered X -ray through one of his experiments, he laid the first foundation for the most common and common diagnostic diagnostic method of clinically.In 1897, X -rays were first used on the military battlefield, during the Balkan War, to find pieces of bullets and broken bones inside the patient's body.
 The detection of X-rays and inventing X-rays is very important in medicine.Currently, X-ray has become a valuable medical tool in diagnosis and treatment of many diseases.It creates a clear image of the musculoskeletal system and some tissue in the body, thereby helping the doctor diagnose, monitor and treat a variety of diseases, especially diseases related to joints and cardiovascular disease., Respiratory.
 So what is the principle to create a X-ray movie, what is the definition of a satisfactory X-ray film, methods and processes to create them?Let's find out with us to find out at this week's meeting of the Burn - Shaping group!
